WEBVTT

00:01.302 --> 00:03.410
Previously on...
Why don't I just marry you?

00:03.434 --> 00:05.087
I've got
a fantastic health plan.

00:05.111 --> 00:06.653
You'd be covered instantly.

00:06.677 --> 00:09.586
Susan got an offer
she couldn't afford to refuse.

00:09.610 --> 00:12.119
You've had too much to drink.
Give me your keys.

00:12.143 --> 00:14.621
Bree rejected a helping hand.

00:14.645 --> 00:16.623
I want to have a baby with you.

00:16.647 --> 00:19.366
Gaby gave Carlos the answer
he'd been waiting for.

00:19.390 --> 00:21.268
You're my second a-b negative
today.

00:21.292 --> 00:23.600
Oh, who is it? That guy.

00:23.624 --> 00:27.404
And Zach began to put
"a" and "b" together.

00:30.661 --> 00:33.040
Susan Mayer had always believed

00:33.064 --> 00:36.683
the punishment
should fit the crime.

00:36.707 --> 00:39.086
She first
came to this conclusion

00:39.110 --> 00:41.348
when she discovered
her husband Karl

00:41.372 --> 00:43.150
had been unfaithful.

00:43.174 --> 00:49.054
Since Karl had destroyed
the love she had given him...

00:52.052 --> 00:54.531
She felt it was appropriate

00:54.555 --> 01:00.467
she destroy the things
he loved in return...

01:00.491 --> 01:03.370
One by one.

01:05.096 --> 01:07.444
But now, three years
after their divorce,

01:07.468 --> 01:11.047
Susan was reunited with Karl
once again...

01:11.071 --> 01:13.280
Susan, are you listening to me?

01:13.304 --> 01:16.123
As partners
in a crime of their own.

01:16.147 --> 01:18.385
This is insurance fraud.
We could both go to jail.

01:18.409 --> 01:20.627
Now we can't tellanyone
we're getting married.

01:20.651 --> 01:22.629
I know. I was listening to you.

01:22.653 --> 01:24.491
Now the prenup's all set.

01:24.515 --> 01:26.493
You can sign it
at the courthouse.

01:26.517 --> 01:28.165
11:30, Wednesday morning. Right?

01:28.189 --> 01:30.167
Right. And your surgery's
still on for Thursday?

01:30.191 --> 01:33.500
Yep. Good. The insurance
kicks in the minute we say "I do."

01:33.524 --> 01:35.242
You're set to go.

01:35.266 --> 01:38.345
I know no one's asking me,
but I think this whole thing

01:38.369 --> 01:39.846
is a tragic mistake,

01:39.870 --> 01:42.649
and I just don't have it in me
to survive another ugly divorce.

01:42.673 --> 01:44.181
Don't worry, honey.

01:44.205 --> 01:46.783
This time, it is strictly a
business arrangement. It better be,

01:46.807 --> 01:49.186
'cause if I see so much
as one lingering gaze

01:49.210 --> 01:51.188
between the two of you,
I swear I'll go

01:51.212 --> 01:53.190
to the insurance company
and turn you in.

01:53.214 --> 01:56.163
So we shouldn't expect
a wedding gift, huh?

01:56.187 --> 01:58.525
Oh, can you grab me
your wedding ring?

01:58.549 --> 02:00.797
I wanna get it cleaned
before the ceremony.

02:00.821 --> 02:04.100
Uh... is that really necessary?

02:04.124 --> 02:07.108
I mean, do we have to do
the whole ring thing?

02:07.132 --> 02:09.136
Of course we do.
It's gotta look believable.

02:09.160 --> 02:10.737
Yeah, okay.

02:10.761 --> 02:13.740
Well, I'll just grab something
out of my jewelry box.

02:13.764 --> 02:15.821
Susan, that ring
was my grandmother's.

02:15.845 --> 02:19.246
One day it's gonna be Julie's.
Where is it?

02:19.270 --> 02:22.149
I don't know...

02:22.173 --> 02:23.190
Exactly.

02:23.214 --> 02:26.358
That was a family heirloom.
I trusted you with it.

02:26.382 --> 02:29.896
Well, I trusted you not to
cheat on me and break my heart.

02:29.920 --> 02:32.629
Oh, my god. Oh, my god.
What... what did you do with it?

02:32.653 --> 02:35.210
I threw it out my car window
somewhere on route 7.

02:35.234 --> 02:37.404
What?! When?

02:37.428 --> 02:39.236
The night you abandoned me.

02:39.260 --> 02:40.607
Suz...

02:40.631 --> 02:42.609
Karl, you aresonot allowed
to get angry.

02:42.633 --> 02:45.312
I mean, I might've been the one
to throw away the wedding ring,

02:45.336 --> 02:46.873
but you threw away
the whole marriage.

02:46.897 --> 02:49.816
There was plenty of bad behavior
that went on back then,

02:49.840 --> 02:51.648
so just get off your high horse.

02:51.672 --> 02:53.650
We're on the same page now,

02:53.674 --> 02:56.684
so we should just focus on that.

03:01.382 --> 03:04.691
Yes, Susan Mayer
believed the punishment

03:04.715 --> 03:06.233
should fit the crime.

03:06.257 --> 03:09.396
Karl, I think
there might be snakes in here.

03:09.420 --> 03:13.400
We're not leaving here
until you find that ring.

03:13.424 --> 03:21.424
But for that matter,
so did Karl.

03:29.540 --> 03:33.820
It was a tradition
at Leonardo's bar and grill,

03:33.844 --> 03:37.301
an hour before closing time,
a waiter would sing a selection

03:37.325 --> 03:40.697
of ridiculously depressing
Italian arias.

03:40.721 --> 03:43.300
It was also a tradition

03:43.324 --> 03:45.781
that the only customers
who would actually listen

03:45.805 --> 03:49.526
were the ones already depressed
to begin with.

03:54.405 --> 03:56.212
Tony?

03:56.236 --> 03:58.415
Do you have to rush off?

03:58.439 --> 04:02.389
I thought maybe we could
just chat for a minute.

04:02.413 --> 04:04.991
So I haven't seen you
in a while.

04:05.015 --> 04:08.325
Well, I didn't wanna come here
because I was afraid

04:08.349 --> 04:10.657
it would drudge up memories
of my husband.

04:10.681 --> 04:13.460
You know, this was our place.

04:13.484 --> 04:15.602
Rex passed away recently.

04:15.626 --> 04:20.406
He was, um, murdered
by our pharmacist.

04:20.430 --> 04:23.340
Wow.

04:23.364 --> 04:25.321
I hope you changed pharmacists.

04:25.345 --> 04:29.276
I didn't have to.
He committed suicide.

04:29.300 --> 04:31.678
Look, you've had
a little too much wine tonight.

04:31.702 --> 04:33.680
How about I call you a cab?

04:33.704 --> 04:35.852
Oh, no, no, no, no. I'm okay.

04:35.876 --> 04:37.854
Your car would be safe
in our lot,

04:37.878 --> 04:42.359
and you can pick it up
tomorrow. Please.

04:42.383 --> 04:43.560
Well, okay.

04:43.584 --> 04:45.362
♪♪♪

04:45.386 --> 04:47.634
Tony?

04:47.658 --> 04:50.337
How many more arias
is he gonna sing?

04:50.361 --> 04:51.398
Five.

04:51.422 --> 04:52.999
Oh. In that case,

04:53.023 --> 04:55.010
why don't you bring me
another bottle

04:55.034 --> 04:56.573
of the Pinot grigio?

04:58.599 --> 05:01.529
And please hurry.

05:48.078 --> 05:49.778
Bree?

05:51.482 --> 05:54.501
Bree. You okay?

05:54.525 --> 05:56.085
Ugh.

05:59.890 --> 06:01.738
Yes?

06:01.762 --> 06:05.472
Hi. Uh, did you know your mother
is asleep on the lawn?

06:07.938 --> 06:10.698
Oh, wow.

06:12.943 --> 06:15.630
Yeah, well, you don't seem
terribly shocked.

06:15.654 --> 06:19.025
Oh, it's, um...
It's just, mom drinks,

06:19.049 --> 06:22.058
and sometimes she sleeps it off
in the weirdest places.

06:22.082 --> 06:24.090
Can I help you with her?

06:24.114 --> 06:26.433
No. No, it's okay.

06:26.457 --> 06:28.935
I, uh, I know how
to take care of her.

06:28.959 --> 06:31.489
Well, good luck to you then.

06:50.441 --> 06:52.459
I wanna play "chopsticks."
Me too.

06:52.483 --> 06:53.960
You okay?

06:53.984 --> 06:55.792
I'm coming!

06:58.689 --> 06:59.666
Hi. Hi.

06:59.690 --> 07:00.867
Your kids...

07:00.891 --> 07:02.869
They have any allergies
I should know about?

07:02.893 --> 07:04.871
Uh, not that I know of. Why?

07:04.895 --> 07:06.873
'Cause I'm watching them.

07:06.897 --> 07:08.875
Tom called,
said you both got pulled

07:08.899 --> 07:12.509
into work for the weekend,
asked me to baby-sit. Really?

07:12.533 --> 07:14.986
I thought it'd be nice
if I gave 'em back to you alive.

07:15.010 --> 07:16.983
Oh, hey,
Mrs. McCluskey.

07:17.007 --> 07:18.545
Hi. Sorry, I forgot to tell you.

07:18.569 --> 07:20.947
Oh, that's okay. Um...

07:20.971 --> 07:24.658
Would you excuse me just
for a second? I have a... thing.

07:24.682 --> 07:26.175
Sure. Thanks.

07:27.718 --> 07:30.218
Follow me.
You're part of the thing.

07:34.885 --> 07:36.863
A million teenagers
in this neighborhood,

07:36.887 --> 07:39.466
and you hire McCluskey?
What's the big deal?

07:39.490 --> 07:41.207
Well, for starters,
she's ancient!

07:41.231 --> 07:43.439
Shh!
This is a thin door!

07:43.463 --> 07:45.942
It was not that long ago
that she keeled over

07:45.966 --> 07:47.844
in her front yard. A day with
our kids will finish the job.

07:47.868 --> 07:49.576
It's only for a few hours.

07:49.600 --> 07:51.548
Plus, Parker's on a play date
with the farrells,

07:51.572 --> 07:53.780
so it's just
the twins and penny.

07:53.804 --> 07:56.182
Justthe twins and penny?

07:56.206 --> 07:58.454
Okay, that was stupid.

07:58.478 --> 08:00.456
Let me try that another way.

08:00.480 --> 08:03.560
We have to be at work
in one hour.

08:03.584 --> 08:05.567
There's no day care
on the weekends,

08:05.591 --> 08:07.734
so you cut McCluskey loose,
we'restuck.

08:07.758 --> 08:09.235
We will find someone...

08:09.259 --> 08:11.738
Someone who doesn't remember
what they were doing

08:11.762 --> 08:13.670
the day Lincoln was shot.

08:13.694 --> 08:17.774
Fine. Let's go break the news.

08:17.798 --> 08:20.498
My wife has something
to tell you.

08:23.033 --> 08:24.911
So here's the deal.

08:24.935 --> 08:27.053
Um, there was
a little miscommunication,

08:27.077 --> 08:29.986
and as it turns out,
we don't need ya.

08:30.010 --> 08:34.490
Okay. Fine.
I'll just go back home.

08:34.514 --> 08:36.491
Okay. Sorry.

08:36.515 --> 08:39.596
By the way,
your husband was right.

08:39.620 --> 08:41.590
It's a thin door.

09:02.843 --> 09:06.653
Carlos, whatare you doing?

09:08.078 --> 09:10.957
Hello, Gabriela.

09:10.981 --> 09:12.659
Oh.

09:12.683 --> 09:14.323
Hi, mom.

09:22.833 --> 09:25.316
I just told Carlos
I justhadto take a shower.

09:25.340 --> 09:27.974
The man next to me on the plane
weighed 300 pounds,

09:27.998 --> 09:30.977
and he sweated all over me.
Ugh, it was so gross.

09:31.001 --> 09:32.979
No, I'm just surprised
you're here.

09:33.003 --> 09:34.681
It's Valentine's day.

09:34.705 --> 09:37.023
Don't you and Mr. Hedge fund
have plans?

09:37.047 --> 09:39.025
I know Carlos and I do.

09:39.049 --> 09:41.628
No, I left Charles.

09:41.652 --> 09:43.259
What? Mm-hmm.

09:43.283 --> 09:45.632
He was worth, like, $6 million.

09:45.656 --> 09:47.033
Money is not everything,
Gabriela.

09:47.057 --> 09:48.735
For some people,

09:48.759 --> 09:50.697
but we're talking
about you now, mother.

09:50.721 --> 09:52.699
You know, I can't believe this.

09:52.723 --> 09:54.706
I mean, I just went through
a terrible breakup,

09:54.730 --> 09:57.744
and the least you could do
is pretend to care.

09:57.768 --> 10:01.678
Well, of course we feel awful
about it, don't we, Gabrielle?

10:01.702 --> 10:04.110
Yeah, we're just sick about it.

10:04.134 --> 10:07.654
Well, don't worry about me.
Mm-hmm. I'll be okay.

10:07.678 --> 10:10.757
In fact, I bought myself
a little gift

10:10.781 --> 10:12.989
to take my mind off my problems.

10:13.013 --> 10:14.700
Really? What did you buy?

10:14.724 --> 10:16.362
New boobs!

10:16.386 --> 10:17.363
Whoa!

10:17.387 --> 10:18.625
No peeking, Carlos.

10:18.649 --> 10:20.627
Okay, mom, put these away!

10:20.651 --> 10:22.629
My plastic surgeon
gave me a great deal.

10:22.653 --> 10:24.070
Aren't they fun?

10:25.756 --> 10:26.926
Bye, Carlos.

10:31.331 --> 10:33.810
What? I think she's charming.

10:33.834 --> 10:36.643
Okay, you can think
she's charming.

10:36.667 --> 10:39.916
But don't forget for one second
thatsheis a monster.

10:43.874 --> 10:46.061
Did you get the gum out
from under the diamond?

10:46.085 --> 10:47.153
Mostly.

10:47.177 --> 10:48.995
Morning.

10:49.019 --> 10:51.719
Hi! Happy Valentine's day.

10:52.753 --> 10:55.802
Dr. Ron,
did you spend the night?

10:55.826 --> 10:58.905
Well, uh, yeah, I got
kinda tired after the movie,

10:58.929 --> 11:01.637
so I asked... it's okay. She
knows that you make house calls.

11:01.661 --> 11:03.940
Oh. Um, so listen,
I've got surgery till 6.

11:03.964 --> 11:06.778
I'll get dressed and I'll pick
you up at about 7.

11:06.802 --> 11:09.816
We have reservations at chez
Naomi. Great! I'll have a light lunch.

11:09.840 --> 11:11.818
And also, Dr. Cunningham's
schedule opened up,

11:11.842 --> 11:15.089
so if you'd like, we can move up
your surgery to Wednesday.

11:15.113 --> 11:18.324
Oh,
I have a wedding that day. On a Wednesday?

11:18.348 --> 11:20.787
Uh... yeah.

11:20.811 --> 11:24.660
Um, wednesdays are becoming
very popular with brides.

11:24.684 --> 11:27.041
It's like the new Saturday.

11:27.065 --> 11:29.035
Oh. Okay.

11:29.059 --> 11:31.037
Well...

11:31.061 --> 11:32.791
I'll see ya tonight. Bye.

11:37.267 --> 11:40.146
Your mother is
a rotten, sneaky person.

11:40.170 --> 11:44.010
Look, I'm not too crazy about
this whole fake marriage thing,

11:44.034 --> 11:47.361
but if you don't have
that operation, you could die.

11:47.385 --> 11:50.216
So don't be so hard on yourself.

11:50.240 --> 11:52.018
Youarea good person.

11:52.042 --> 11:55.291
Thanks, hon. That really helps.

11:55.315 --> 11:57.293
Okay, now I want you to go over

11:57.317 --> 11:59.295
and slip this ring
to your father.

11:59.319 --> 12:01.768
And just so you know,
if Edie catches you,

12:01.792 --> 12:04.222
I'm expecting you to swallow it.

12:08.428 --> 12:11.137
How's the hangover?

12:11.161 --> 12:14.941
I do not have a hangover,
Andrew, because I was not drunk.

12:16.406 --> 12:19.415
Then, uh... how about
a little hair of the dog?

12:19.439 --> 12:21.948
It'll perk you right up.

12:21.972 --> 12:24.050
Look, for the record,

12:24.074 --> 12:27.958
I had an allergic reaction
to my antihistamine medication,

12:27.982 --> 12:30.957
so I would appreciate
just a little bit of sympathy.

12:30.981 --> 12:34.000
Why can't you just drink alone
in your room like Tammy's mom?

12:34.024 --> 12:36.763
For god sakes,
it was an honest mistake.

12:36.787 --> 12:38.104
I thought I could have

12:38.128 --> 12:40.106
just a little bit of wine
with dinner,

12:40.130 --> 12:42.760
but, apparently,
my body couldn't handle it.

12:47.037 --> 12:48.344
Fine!

12:48.368 --> 12:50.977
If it makes everybody happy,
I will just suffer

12:51.001 --> 12:53.980
through my sneezing fits
and my hives on my own.

12:55.505 --> 12:56.953
There. Is that better?

12:56.977 --> 12:59.055
So basically
you would rather drink

12:59.079 --> 13:00.979
than to not have allergies?

13:07.787 --> 13:11.017
Hi. Is now a bad time?
I could really use a favor.

13:18.428 --> 13:20.376
She was beautiful, wasn't she?

13:20.400 --> 13:23.509
Yeah.

13:23.533 --> 13:26.043
Come on, sit down.
Your breakfast is getting cold.

13:36.116 --> 13:39.065
Was my real mother beautiful?

13:39.089 --> 13:43.930
Well, she was, uh,
attractive, as I recall.

13:43.954 --> 13:46.802
Do I look like her?

13:46.826 --> 13:50.406
I don't know.
I-I only met her once.

13:50.430 --> 13:52.909
Oh. Well, 'cause if
I don't look like her,

13:52.933 --> 13:55.373
then I might look like
my real dad.

13:58.568 --> 14:01.848
I'm getting real tired
of your morbid fascination

14:01.872 --> 14:06.122
with two strangers who didn't
love you enough to keep you.

14:06.146 --> 14:08.276
So, please,
stop asking about them.

14:10.380 --> 14:13.529
It's only natural that I'd wanna
talk about my birth parents.

14:13.553 --> 14:16.332
Well, it may be natural,

14:16.356 --> 14:18.334
but it certainly isn't polite.

14:22.993 --> 14:25.316
And once
your daughter was dead,

14:25.340 --> 14:27.413
they had to get rid
of her somehow.

14:27.437 --> 14:30.046
That's where
the toy chest came in.

14:30.070 --> 14:31.918
Flash forward 15 years,

14:31.942 --> 14:35.329
the chest washes up
on the shore of rockwater lake.

14:35.353 --> 14:38.254
Any forensic evidence
is long gone,

14:38.278 --> 14:40.586
and the youngs
get away with murder.

14:40.610 --> 14:43.559
Now, of course,
the wife, Mary Alice,

14:43.583 --> 14:46.162
is already dead, but...

14:46.186 --> 14:48.965
Paul young's a different matter.

14:48.989 --> 14:52.868
If you'd like me
to deal with him,

14:52.892 --> 14:55.942
just say the word.

14:55.966 --> 14:59.946
Delfino's bringing
my grandson here.

14:59.970 --> 15:03.009
I wanna get the kid something.

15:03.033 --> 15:05.543
You know anything
about those mp3 things?

15:07.978 --> 15:11.317
Yeah, they're real nice.
I'd go with that.

15:11.341 --> 15:15.992
Ah, he's probably
got one already.

15:16.016 --> 15:17.994
Paul young has had 16 years

15:18.018 --> 15:20.118
to get my grandkid
anything he wants.

15:22.522 --> 15:25.531
Do me a favor, will ya? Yeah.

15:25.555 --> 15:28.174
See to it that Paul young

15:28.198 --> 15:32.028
has a toy chest of his very own.

15:49.649 --> 15:51.597
Karl!

15:51.621 --> 15:55.001
Yeah? This
place is a freakin' pigsty.

15:55.025 --> 15:57.163
Would you get down here
and help me?

15:57.187 --> 15:59.405
All right, hold on,
it's almost halftime.

15:59.429 --> 16:01.307
By the way,
I made dinner reservations

16:01.331 --> 16:03.409
at chez Naomi tonight,
if that's okay.

16:03.433 --> 16:05.650
It's gotta be better
than that rathole

16:05.674 --> 16:08.044
you took me to on new year's.

16:08.068 --> 16:10.346
And don't eventhink
of getting me carnations again.

16:10.370 --> 16:13.019
That crap might have flown
for Mayer.

16:13.043 --> 16:15.030
I actually have taste.

16:15.054 --> 16:16.505
Come on! Move it!

16:25.085 --> 16:28.664
All right, I'm coming.

16:28.688 --> 16:30.997
No! No, no, no.
Sit and watch the game.

16:31.021 --> 16:32.968
I was just giving you
a hard time.

16:32.992 --> 16:35.671
You'd had a tough week.

16:35.695 --> 16:37.673
♪♪♪

16:37.697 --> 16:39.005
Boys...

16:39.029 --> 16:41.307
Can you just keep it down
just a little bit?

16:41.331 --> 16:43.309
Because I have a very...

16:43.333 --> 16:46.112
Uh, special type
of grown-up headache.

16:46.136 --> 16:50.116
We need to see mommy and daddy.
We wanna play 'em our song.

16:50.140 --> 16:51.417
Honey, you can't.
They're at work.

16:51.441 --> 16:54.120
Well, can we play it for you?

16:54.144 --> 16:56.522
♪♪♪

16:56.546 --> 17:00.626
Sure.

17:00.650 --> 17:03.190
Just... just a moment, okay?

17:04.454 --> 17:08.002
Ohh.

17:08.027 --> 17:10.005
All right, boys, let's have it.

17:10.029 --> 17:13.499
♪♪♪

17:19.108 --> 17:22.188
When I heard that you two
wanted to try for another child,

17:22.212 --> 17:23.489
I was delighted.

17:23.512 --> 17:26.122
But I had some cause
for concern.

17:26.146 --> 17:29.195
Gabrielle, you suffered
some extensive injuries

17:29.219 --> 17:30.496
during your fall last month,

17:30.520 --> 17:34.220
and the test confirmed
there are complications.

17:36.426 --> 17:38.164
You can't have kids?

17:38.188 --> 17:40.266
Well, the doctor's not
100% positive,

17:40.290 --> 17:42.138
but it's very, very iffy.

17:42.162 --> 17:43.439
Carlos, I am so sorry.

17:43.463 --> 17:46.112
I know how much
you wanted to be a dad.

17:46.136 --> 17:47.413
Thanks.

17:47.437 --> 17:50.646
